1
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:08,180
永远的蝙蝠侠

2
00:01:51,120 --> 00:01:54,180
要带个三明治吗?
Can I persuade you to take a sandwich?

3
00:01:54,260 --> 00:01:56,510
我会买"外带"在车上吃
I'll get drive-through.

4
00:02:37,140 --> 00:02:40,440
你想靠那正义使者来救你?
You're counting on the winged avenger to deliver you from evil...

5
00:02:40,440 --> 00:02:42,620
是吧? 老兄!
...aren't you, my friend?

6
00:02:43,940 --> 00:02:45,510
你要杀我吗?
Are you going to kill me?

7
00:02:45,510 --> 00:02:49,440
那倒不一定  我们还没决定好
Maybe, maybe not. We're of two minds on the subject.

8
00:02:52,090 --> 00:02:54,230
赌一把怎么样?
You a gambling man?

9
00:02:54,920 --> 00:02:57,630
来丢铜板决定如何?
What say we flip for it?

10
00:02:57,830 --> 00:03:01,060
有人生来是英雄  有人是狗熊
One man is born a hero, his brother a coward.

11
00:03:01,060 --> 00:03:04,770
朱门酒肉臭  路有冻死骨
Babies starve, politicians grow fat...

12
00:03:04,770 --> 00:03:08,900
黄钟毁弃  瓦斧雷鸣
...holy men are martyred, and junkies grow legion.

13
00:03:08,900 --> 00:03:10,370
为什么?
Why?

14
00:03:10,370 --> 00:03:13,000
为什么? 为什么? 为什么?
Why, why, why, why, why?

15
00:03:14,310 --> 00:03:15,480
狗屎运!
Luck!

16
00:03:15,480 --> 00:03:21,930
盲目愚蠢! 毫无理由的狗屎运
Blind, stupid, simple, doo-dah... clueless luck!

17
00:03:24,850 --> 00:03:29,260
只有丢铜板才有公平可言
The random toss... is the only true justice.

18
00:03:29,260 --> 00:03:35,000
看看你老兄这回运气如何?
Let's see what justice has in store... for you.

19
00:03:40,140 --> 00:03:42,210
一切交给上帝吧!
It's like the touch of God.

20
00:03:42,210 --> 00:03:43,790
等一下!
Wait, wait, wait.

21
00:03:47,140 --> 00:03:48,550
你狗运不赖嘛!
Fortune smiles. Another day of wine and roses.

22
00:03:48,550 --> 00:03:51,980
该喝啤酒吃披萨庆祝
In your case, beer and pizza.

23
00:03:51,980 --> 00:03:53,780
喂! 我们该出发了
Out of here, guys!

24
00:03:53,780 --> 00:03:56,520
-你说你会让我活命  -没错
-But you said you'd let me live! -Too true!

25
00:03:56,520 --> 00:04:00,260
留你当活饵  引诱那只大蝙蝠  太酷了!
And so you shall! Nothing's better than live bait to trap a bat.

26
00:04:16,200 --> 00:04:17,690
真精彩的出场
Hot entrance.

27
00:04:18,280 --> 00:04:19,380
双面人吗?
Two-Face?

28
00:04:19,380 --> 00:04:20,710
两名警卫丧生
2 guards are dead.

29
00:04:20,710 --> 00:04:23,150
警方没料到他会挟持人质
He's holding a third hostage. Didn't see this one coming.

30
00:04:23,150 --> 00:04:24,650
我们早该想到
We should have.

31
00:04:24,650 --> 00:04:26,380
高谭市第二银行
The 2nd Bank of Gotham.

32
00:04:26,380 --> 00:04:28,620
我逮捕他的两周年纪念
2nd anniversary of the day I captured him.

33
00:04:28,620 --> 00:04:30,390
难怪他要再犯案
How could he resist?

34
00:04:30,390 --> 00:04:31,820
我是梅慈丝
I'm Chase Meridian.

35
00:04:31,820 --> 00:04:35,060
我请她担任本案顾问  她是...
I asked her to come to here to consuIt on the case. She specializes in--

36
00:04:35,060 --> 00:04:39,800
心理学  多重人格理论专家  我早已拜读大作
Psychology, multiple personalities. I read your work.

37
00:04:39,800 --> 00:04:41,100
见解独到!
Insightful.

38
00:04:41,100 --> 00:04:42,900
很天真  不过见解独特!
Naive, but insightful.

39
00:04:42,900 --> 00:04:44,500
真令我受宠若惊
I'm flattered.

40
00:04:44,500 --> 00:04:47,010
不是每个女人都能有此殊荣的
Not every girl makes a superhero's night table.

41
00:04:47,010 --> 00:04:48,170
能跟他讲道理吗?
Can we reason with him?

42
00:04:48,170 --> 00:04:51,140
-他手里有人质  -和他谈判有用
-He's got innocent people up there. -It won't do any good.

43
00:04:51,140 --> 00:04:54,220
-这家伙杀人不眨眼  -我同意
-He'll slaughter them without a thought. -Agreed.

44
00:04:54,280 --> 00:04:57,550
心灵的重创令他人格产生分裂
A trauma powerful enough to create an alternate personality leaves one--

45
00:04:57,550 --> 00:05:00,790
社会的规则秩序完全置之不理
In a world where normal rules of right and wrong no longer apply.

46
00:05:00,790 --> 00:05:01,820
完全正确
Exactly.

47
00:05:01,860 --> 00:05:03,960
就像你一样
Like you.

48
00:05:03,960 --> 00:05:06,490
我可以好好写一本书来探讨
I could write a hell of a paper

49
00:05:06,490 --> 00:05:09,930
一个男人为何穿得像啮齿动物
on a grown man dressing like a flying rodent.

50
00:05:09,930 --> 00:05:13,230
蝙蝠不是啮齿动物  梅医生
Bats aren't rodents, Dr. Meridian.

51
00:05:13,230 --> 00:05:15,500
真的? 这我倒不知道
Really? I didn't know that.

52
00:05:15,500 --> 00:05:17,970
你真有意思
You are interesting.

53
00:05:19,670 --> 00:05:21,690
叫我慈丝
And call me Chase.

54
00:05:23,540 --> 00:05:24,850
对了  你贵姓?
By the way, do you have a first name,

55
00:05:24,850 --> 00:05:27,440
或者我可以称你蝙蝠吗?
or do I call you Bats?

56
00:05:33,090 --> 00:05:35,160
让我们玩个痛快吧?
Start the party with a bang!

57
00:05:44,270 --> 00:05:47,140
连送死都这么准时
Very punctual, even for his own funeral. Boys!

58
00:05:47,140 --> 00:05:49,840
兄弟们  宰了他!
Kill the Bat!

59
00:06:01,220 --> 00:06:02,840
开枪!
Blast him!

60
00:06:15,030 --> 00:06:17,080
芝麻开门!
Open sesame.

61
00:07:21,570 --> 00:07:22,960
这是陷阱!
It's a trap!

62
00:07:57,370 --> 00:08:00,740
各位亲爱的高谭市民请注意
Attention citizens of fair Gotham!

63
00:08:02,880 --> 00:08:05,050
等我们开了保险箱
When we open that safe,

64
00:08:05,050 --> 00:08:06,820
什么就都有了
we'll have everything we ever wanted...

65
00:08:06,820 --> 00:08:11,300
足够让高谭市天下大乱
...enough cash to rain down upon fair Gotham a glorious flood of chaos.

66
00:08:12,390 --> 00:08:17,110
当然  你这龟儿子是死定了
And, of course... you, my boy, dead!

67
00:08:19,260 --> 00:08:21,800
那是强酸液体
It's boiling acid!

68
00:08:22,060 --> 00:08:23,720
为了让你死得愉快
For your dying pleasure,

69
00:08:23,730 --> 00:08:26,310
请享用美味大补汤
we are serving the acid that made us the men we are!

70
00:08:30,810 --> 00:08:31,740
抓牢了
Hold on.

71
00:08:35,250 --> 00:08:36,530
吊走
Haul away!

72
00:08:36,880 --> 00:08:38,750
快吊走
Yes! Haul away!

73
00:08:44,320 --> 00:08:45,010
手给我
Give me your hand.

74
00:08:45,020 --> 00:08:46,480
别放手哇!
Don't let go!

75
00:08:52,400 --> 00:08:53,930
这东西给我
I must borrow this.

76
00:08:57,000 --> 00:08:59,330
那是我的助听器
That's my hearing aid!

77
00:08:59,480 --> 00:09:00,550
谢谢
Thanks.

78
00:09:05,010 --> 00:09:08,340
天啊  我的鞋子要溶化了
Wow! My shoes are melting!

79
00:09:17,030 --> 00:09:18,420
救命!
No more!

80
00:09:34,170 --> 00:09:35,510
抓紧了
Hang on.

81
00:09:35,510 --> 00:09:36,860
抓紧?
Hang on?

82
00:09:58,470 --> 00:10:01,270
快让他下来
Get him down. Get him down.

83
00:10:01,270 --> 00:10:03,970
快  小心点
Take it easy with him.

84
00:10:04,310 --> 00:10:05,550
你没事的
You'll be all right.

85
00:10:05,570 --> 00:10:06,640
放轻松
Just stay calm.

86
00:10:06,670 --> 00:10:09,630
小心! 让他慢慢下来

87
00:10:18,890 --> 00:10:20,760
这下他没救了!
This'll fix him!

88
00:10:27,360 --> 00:10:28,750
抓牢啊!
Hang on!

89
00:10:49,690 --> 00:10:51,560
我来仔细瞧瞧
Let's see.

90
00:10:51,560 --> 00:10:53,020
太棒了!
Yes!

91
00:10:53,020 --> 00:10:56,740
是...多么快乐的一天
Yes, yes, yes, yes, yes, yes! Oh, happy day!

92
00:10:58,130 --> 00:11:02,850
向那只尖耳的夜行鼠辈永别了
Farewell forever to that... pointy-eared night rat!

93
00:11:04,730 --> 00:11:06,020
双面人
Face!

94
00:11:30,200 --> 00:11:33,530
你需要心理治疗  投降吧!
You need help. Give it up.

95
00:11:55,560 --> 00:11:59,060
这次让你死得有点品味
Have the good taste to die!

96
00:11:59,060 --> 00:12:00,340
再见了
See you!

97
00:12:40,970 --> 00:12:43,840
尽管昨晚蝙蝠侠奋不顾身追捕
Despite a valiant effort last night by Batman...

98
00:12:43,840 --> 00:12:47,840
危险人物双面人仍侥幸逃脱
...Harvey Two-Face is still at large and extremely dangerous.

99
00:12:47,840 --> 00:12:49,310
其他新闻方面
And another news today...

100
00:12:49,310 --> 00:12:53,320
富豪布鲁斯韦恩将利润分红
...billionaire Bruce Wayne extended his profit-sharing program...

101
00:12:53,320 --> 00:12:57,590
奖励企业内电子部门员工
...to the employees of the successful electronics branch of Wayne Enterprises.

102
00:13:08,500 --> 00:13:10,090
韦恩先生
Mr. Wayne.

103
00:13:10,730 --> 00:13:14,170
大驾光临  本部门无上光荣
Your inspections are a departmental highlight.

104
00:13:14,170 --> 00:13:16,670
天啊  是他
Oh, my God, it's him.

105
00:13:18,070 --> 00:13:20,340
勇敢一点  勇敢一点
I am a winner. I am a winner.

106
00:13:20,340 --> 00:13:22,250
不要紧张
I am a winner.

107
00:13:22,250 --> 00:13:23,840
勇敢一点
I am a winner.

108
00:13:25,720 --> 00:13:29,390
这是最新科技生化治疗器
Bioremediation. Alternative fuel.

109
00:13:29,390 --> 00:13:31,320
韦恩先生  时候不早了
Mr. Wayne, look at that time.

110
00:13:31,320 --> 00:13:34,550
请到研发部参观吧
Perhaps we should get to R & D as soon as possible.

111
00:13:35,430 --> 00:13:36,980
你是...
Mister...?

112
00:13:38,530 --> 00:13:40,500
奥! 布鲁斯韦恩
Oh, Bruce Wayne.

113
00:13:40,500 --> 00:13:43,440
那是我  阁下是?
No, that's my name. And you are?

114
00:13:43,440 --> 00:13:44,740
尼格玛
Nygma.

115
00:13:44,740 --> 00:13:46,040
艾德华
Edward.

116
00:13:46,040 --> 00:13:48,970
是您亲自雇用我的
Edward Nygma. You hired me personally.

117
00:13:48,970 --> 00:13:51,210
我都这么告诉别人
Just like I tell everyone.

118
00:13:51,210 --> 00:13:53,110
事实上我们倒没见过面
We've never actually met,

119
00:13:53,110 --> 00:13:57,240
不过你的名字在我雇用合约上
but your name was on the hiring slip. I have it.

120
00:13:57,320 --> 00:13:59,480
请把手还我
I need that hand.

121
00:13:59,480 --> 00:14:01,490
奥  是的
Oh, yes, of course.

122
00:14:01,490 --> 00:14:03,020
抱歉
I'm sorry.

123
00:14:03,350 --> 00:14:04,900
因为您是
It's just that...

124
00:14:05,930 --> 00:14:07,960
您是我的偶像...
...you're my idol.

125
00:14:07,960 --> 00:14:09,230
去工作
Get to work.

126
00:14:09,230 --> 00:14:12,770
有人一直不肯让我们见面
And some people have been trying to keep us apart.

127
00:14:12,770 --> 00:14:14,430
回去工作
Back to work.

128
00:14:14,430 --> 00:14:15,870
没关系
It's okay.

129
00:14:15,870 --> 00:14:17,940
你在想什么?
What's on your mind?

130
00:14:17,940 --> 00:14:19,410
完全正确
Precisely.

131
00:14:19,410 --> 00:14:21,740
我们都在想些什么?
What's on all our minds?

132
00:14:21,740 --> 00:14:23,760
脑波...
Brain waves.

133
00:14:28,050 --> 00:14:34,320
韦恩企业集团未来希望之所系
The future... of Wayne Enterprises... is brain waves.

134
00:14:35,660 --> 00:14:36,960
真抱歉  韦恩先生
I must apologize, Mr. Wayne.

135
00:14:36,960 --> 00:14:39,630
我今天终止了他的研究计划
I terminated his project today.

136
00:14:39,630 --> 00:14:41,030
没关系
It's okay.

137
00:14:41,030 --> 00:14:42,800
我这边有
I have it!

138
00:14:51,940 --> 00:14:53,270
我的发明
My invention...

139
00:14:53,270 --> 00:14:57,750
将电视讯号发射入人脑中
...beams any TV signal directly into the human brain.

140
00:14:57,750 --> 00:15:01,550
借刺激中子以操控脑波
By stimulating neurons, manipulating brain waves...

141
00:15:01,550 --> 00:15:04,220
这机器可让他电视观众
...this device makes the audience

142
00:15:04,220 --> 00:15:07,860
仿佛成为剧中人物身历其境
feel like they're inside the show.

143
00:15:07,860 --> 00:15:10,530
完全忘却俗世纷扰
Why be brutalized by an uncaring world?

144
00:15:10,530 --> 00:15:14,520
你刚刚说"操控脑波"吗?
Did you say "manipulating brain waves?"

145
00:15:16,630 --> 00:15:18,220
是的
Yes.

146
00:15:19,040 --> 00:15:20,140
不过...
But...

147
00:15:20,140 --> 00:15:24,240
像您这种大人物不会需要的
...someone like you would never need it.

148
00:15:24,240 --> 00:15:31,010
如此聪明  机智  迷人的名人
Someone so... intelligent, witty and... charming.

149
00:15:31,010 --> 00:15:33,920
我需要资金来作人体实验
I need a bit of additional funding for human trials.

150
00:15:33,920 --> 00:15:36,020
来  我来示范
Let me show you, please!

151
00:15:36,020 --> 00:15:39,960
我要看详细的设计计划
Now, listen... I want a full set of schematics on this, okay?

152
00:15:39,960 --> 00:15:42,830
布鲁斯  我们会成为合作伙伴
We'll be full partners in this, Bruce.

153
00:15:42,830 --> 00:15:46,330
你看  我们是天生最佳拍挡
Look at us! Two of a kind!

154
00:15:46,330 --> 00:15:49,840
打电话给我助理  她会安排
You call my assistant, Margaret. She'll set something up.

155
00:15:49,970 --> 00:15:53,590
很明显  你在敷衍我
That's not... going to be good for me.

156
00:15:54,110 --> 00:15:56,940
给我一个肯定的答案
I need an answer now.

157
00:15:56,940 --> 00:15:59,310
这是我该得的
I think I deserve it.

158
00:15:59,310 --> 00:16:02,750
抱歉  你的要求恕难同意
I'm sorry, then the answer is no.

159
00:16:02,750 --> 00:16:05,180
干扰人类脑波
Tampering with people's brain waves...

160
00:16:05,180 --> 00:16:07,620
思想操控机器
...mind manipulation...

161
00:16:07,620 --> 00:16:10,790
恐怕会引起轩然大波
...it just raises too many questions.

162
00:16:10,790 --> 00:16:12,070
抱歉
Sorry.

163
00:16:12,090 --> 00:16:15,420
多谢大家  谢谢你们的努力
Thanks, keep up the good work. Looks great.

164
00:16:15,490 --> 00:16:16,730
好了  各位
All right, everyone!

165
00:16:16,730 --> 00:16:18,330
继续工作
Back to work!

166
00:16:18,330 --> 00:16:21,000
等一下再跟你算帐
We'll discuss this later!

167
00:16:25,010 --> 00:16:28,650
你怎么可以让我失望
You were supposed to understand.

168
00:16:31,810 --> 00:16:35,220
我会让你认识清楚
I'll make you understand.

169
00:16:38,620 --> 00:16:40,040
锁上
Lock.

170
00:16:46,290 --> 00:16:47,650
启动
Chair.

171
00:16:56,370 --> 00:16:58,970
讯号收到
I saw the signal.

172
00:16:58,970 --> 00:17:00,880
一切准备就绪
All is ready.

173
00:17:40,780 --> 00:17:42,390
局长  他人呢?
Commissioner?

174
00:17:42,390 --> 00:17:43,880
他回家了
He's home.

175
00:17:44,790 --> 00:17:47,620
是我发的讯号
I sent the signal.

176
00:17:47,620 --> 00:17:49,680
怎么回事?
What's wrong?

177
00:17:51,660 --> 00:17:55,070
昨晚我注意到双面人一件事
Last night I noticed something about Two-Face:

178
00:17:55,070 --> 00:17:56,690
他的铜板
his coin.

179
00:17:56,700 --> 00:17:58,440
那是他的弱点
It's his Achilles' heel.

180
00:17:58,440 --> 00:18:00,140
可以好好研究一下
It can be exploited.

181
00:18:00,140 --> 00:18:01,970
我知道了
I know.

182
00:18:01,970 --> 00:18:03,910
你叫我来就为了这个?
You called me for this?

183
00:18:03,910 --> 00:18:06,580
我的呼叫器可不是BB机
The Batsignal is not a beeper.

184
00:18:06,580 --> 00:18:11,300
你对我的吸引力不只在公事上
I wish I could say that my interest in you was... purely professional.

185
00:18:11,450 --> 00:18:13,820
你在挑逗我吗?
You trying to get under my cape?

186
00:18:13,820 --> 00:18:17,420
女人整天研究精神病很寂寞的
A girl can't live by psychoses alone.

187
00:18:17,420 --> 00:18:20,860
是那部车吧? 马子喜欢搔包车
It's the car, right? Chicks love it.

188
00:18:20,860 --> 00:18:24,030
为什么坏男人总是吸引着我
What is it about the wrong kind of man?

189
00:18:24,030 --> 00:18:27,230
高中时是戴耳环的痞子
In grade school: guys with earrings.

190
00:18:27,230 --> 00:18:30,470
大学是骑机车  穿皮夹克的
College: motorcycles, leather jackets.

191
00:18:30,470 --> 00:18:32,720
现在嘛...
Now...

192
00:18:34,870 --> 00:18:37,740
黑色橡皮衣的男子
...black rubber.

193
00:18:37,740 --> 00:18:40,930
试试救火员  脱衣服比较方便
Try a fireman. Less to take off.

194
00:18:42,310 --> 00:18:43,670
这我不在乎
I don't mind the work.

195
00:18:43,680 --> 00:18:45,850
只可惜看不到你的真面目
Pity I can't see behind the mask.

196
00:18:45,850 --> 00:18:47,650
每个人都戴着面具过日子
We all wear masks.

197
00:18:47,650 --> 00:18:49,590
我的生命是本打开的书
My life's an open book.

198
00:18:49,590 --> 00:18:51,090
想看看吗
You read?

199
00:18:51,090 --> 00:18:53,630
我不想在人家家里野餐
I don't blend in at a family picnic.

200
00:18:54,790 --> 00:18:58,990
我们可以试试  我会准备酒
We could give it a try. I'll bring the wine...

201
00:18:59,100 --> 00:19:02,360
你带着你受创的灵魂前来
...you bring your scarred psyche.

202
00:19:03,470 --> 00:19:05,440
你很主动  是吧?
Direct, aren't you?

203
00:19:05,440 --> 00:19:07,040
你喜欢主动的女人
You like strong women.

204
00:19:07,040 --> 00:19:08,780
我对你研究过
I've done my homework.

205
00:19:08,780 --> 00:19:12,710
还是要我穿紧身衣带皮鞭?
Or do I need skintight vinyl and a whip?

206
00:19:12,710 --> 00:19:15,450
我对女人向来不在行
I haven't had much luck with women.

207
00:19:15,450 --> 00:19:18,400
也许是对象不适合
Maybe you just haven't met the right woman.

208
00:19:24,330 --> 00:19:25,460
我收到了讯号
I saw the signal.

209
00:19:25,460 --> 00:19:26,460
怎么呢?
What's going on?

210
00:19:26,460 --> 00:19:28,160
没事
Nothing.

211
00:19:28,700 --> 00:19:30,500
真的没事
False alarm.

212
00:19:30,500 --> 00:19:32,030
是吗?
Are you sure?

213
00:19:51,050 --> 00:19:52,260
女人啊!
Women.

214
00:20:02,370 --> 00:20:03,950
成功了!
Now I've got it!

215
00:20:07,600 --> 00:20:10,150
轩然大波  引起轩然大波
Too many questions. There's too many questions.

216
00:20:10,150 --> 00:20:13,610
轩然大波...
Too many....

217
00:20:13,610 --> 00:20:15,380
我就证明给你看
I'll show you it works!

218
00:20:15,380 --> 00:20:17,780
你到底在胡搞什么
What the hell is going on here?!

219
00:20:17,780 --> 00:20:19,820
这个计划已经被终止
I told you this project is terminated!

220
00:20:19,820 --> 00:20:22,070
我要叫警卫来
I'm calling security!

221
00:20:27,690 --> 00:20:29,870
咖啡因有碍你健康
Caffeine will kill you!

222
00:20:34,270 --> 00:20:36,900
天鼠先生  醒来吧
Rise and shine, little guinea pig.

223
00:20:36,900 --> 00:20:38,500
你在干嘛!
What are you doing?

224
00:20:38,500 --> 00:20:39,840
快放了我
Untie me!

225
00:20:39,840 --> 00:20:41,610
反正又不会痛
This won't hurt.

226
00:20:41,610 --> 00:20:44,280
至少我是这样认为
Least, I don't think it will.

227
00:20:45,180 --> 00:20:46,610
你在干嘛?
What are you doing?

228
00:20:46,610 --> 00:20:49,680
你敢碰那开关...
You touch that switch and--

229
00:20:49,680 --> 00:20:51,180
这个吗?
This?

230
00:21:06,400 --> 00:21:08,230
画面不见了
Losing resolution.

231
00:21:08,230 --> 00:21:09,790
能量加强
More power!

232
00:21:33,230 --> 00:21:35,000
艾德华尼格玛
Edward Nygma!

233
00:21:35,000 --> 00:21:36,830
请准备上场
You're the next contestant on...

234
00:21:36,830 --> 00:21:40,470
脑力激荡超级秀
...Brain Drain!

235
00:21:40,970 --> 00:21:45,430
我选看起来笨头笨脑的1号
I'll take what's inside thick skull number one!

236
00:21:45,440 --> 00:21:48,110
他能得到什么大奖
What have we got for him?

237
00:21:48,110 --> 00:21:52,310
史帝雷  这是我研究的大突破
Oh, Stickley, I'm having a breakthrough!

238
00:21:52,310 --> 00:21:53,950
你准备抓狂吧
And a breakdown!

239
00:21:53,950 --> 00:21:56,380
反正我是个大天才
Nevertheless, I'm smarter. I'm a genius.

240
00:21:56,750 --> 00:21:59,490
不对  是超级天才
No, several geniuses.

241
00:21:59,490 --> 00:22:05,460
比弗洛依德还厉害的旷世奇才
A gaggle, a swarm... a flock of freaking Freuds!

242
00:22:05,460 --> 00:22:07,930
猜猜看
Riddle me this, Fred.

243
00:22:07,930 --> 00:22:10,330
什么东西对一个人很重要
What is everything to someone...

244
00:22:10,330 --> 00:22:12,770
对别人却微不足道?
...and nothing to everyone else?

245
00:22:12,770 --> 00:22:14,970
是您老兄的智力
Your mind, baby!

246
00:22:14,970 --> 00:22:17,510
现在我俩智力将彼此共享
Now mine pumps with the power of yours!

247
00:22:17,510 --> 00:22:21,340
你的智慧归我所有
I'm sucking up your lQ

248
00:22:21,340 --> 00:22:25,230
我会把你的大脑皮质
Vacuuming your cortex

249
00:22:29,690 --> 00:22:31,740
吸得一干二净
Feeding off your brain

250
00:22:51,440 --> 00:22:53,420
太刺激了!
What a rush!

251
00:22:54,350 --> 00:22:56,400
发生什么事?
What just happened?

252
00:22:58,950 --> 00:23:01,850
一点小小的副作用
A very surprising side effect.

253
00:23:01,850 --> 00:23:05,790
当您沉醉在我的立体电视之时
While you were mesmerized by my 3-D TV...

254
00:23:05,790 --> 00:23:09,090
我用你中枢能量让我更聪明了
...l used your neural energy to grow smarter.

255
00:23:09,090 --> 00:23:11,830
大老板说得没错
Bruce Wayne was right!

256
00:23:11,830 --> 00:23:15,130
你这个疯子  怪胎
You demented, bizarre, unethical toad!

257
00:23:15,170 --> 00:23:17,500
这是非法脑波干扰
It is brain manipulation!

258
00:23:17,500 --> 00:23:18,900
我要检举你
I'm reporting you to the FCC!

259
00:23:18,900 --> 00:23:21,740
非法从事人体实验!
The human experimentation board! The AMl!

260
00:23:21,740 --> 00:23:23,840
我会向警方报告
And the police!

261
00:23:23,840 --> 00:23:26,080
你准备坐牢吧!
You are going up on charges...

262
00:23:26,080 --> 00:23:31,110
我看你也得进疯人院
...to court, to jail... and then to a mental institution forever!

263
00:23:31,120 --> 00:23:35,350
你现在就被开除了! 滚吧!
But, first and foremost, Nygma, you are fired!

264
00:23:35,350 --> 00:23:37,640
听到吗? 快滚吧!
Do you hear me? Fired!

265
00:23:42,160 --> 00:23:44,520
那可不一定
I don't think so.

266
00:23:57,550 --> 00:23:59,100
救命啊!
Help!

267
00:24:02,920 --> 00:24:04,130
抓紧啊!
Hang on!

268
00:24:07,890 --> 00:24:09,160
老兄!
Babe!

269
00:24:09,160 --> 00:24:12,560
你被开除了!
You are fired!

270
00:24:13,230 --> 00:24:15,530
或者该说是...
Or should I say...

271
00:24:15,530 --> 00:24:17,480
被"终结"了?
...terminated?

272
00:24:21,970 --> 00:24:24,600
再见了  蠢才
Surf's up, Big Kahuna!

273
00:24:28,280 --> 00:24:31,310
姿势不错  可惜落水不佳
Nice form, but rough on the landing.

274
00:24:31,310 --> 00:24:33,910
大概只能得铜牌
He may have to settle for the Bronze.

275
00:24:38,420 --> 00:24:41,260
猜个谜语  韦恩先生
Questions, Mr. Wayne?

276
00:24:41,260 --> 00:24:45,300
我的实验会造成轩然大波
My work raises too many questions.

277
00:24:45,300 --> 00:24:51,110
怎么没人给你好好上一课呢?
Why hasn't anybody... put you in your place?

278
00:24:52,940 --> 00:24:55,670
前任高谭市首席检察官丹特
Harvey Dent, once Gotham's District Attorney...

279
00:24:55,670 --> 00:24:59,110
在法庭上遭黑社会以毒液毁容
...was horribly scarred by underworld kingpin, Boss Moroni.

280
00:24:59,110 --> 00:25:01,210
蝙蝠侠曾企图阻止不及
Although Batman tried to save him...

281
00:25:01,210 --> 00:25:03,510
丹特左半脸严重毁损
...Dent's left-brain damage

282
00:25:03,510 --> 00:25:06,450
心理失衡导致他成为知名罪犯
turned him into a violent criminal...

283
00:25:06,450 --> 00:25:08,520
并归咎蝙蝠侠誓言报复
...who blamed Batman and who has vowed to destroy him.

284
00:25:08,520 --> 00:25:10,850
双面人现为超级要犯
Harvey Two-Face is extremely dangerous,

285
00:25:10,850 --> 00:25:13,260
请大家提高警觉
repeat, extremely dangerous.

286
00:25:13,260 --> 00:25:15,030
局长来电
That was the Commissioner.

287
00:25:15,030 --> 00:25:17,850
公司里出意外了
There's been an accident at Wayne Enterprises.

288
00:25:19,820 --> 00:25:21,520
死得真惨
Horrible way to die.

289
00:25:21,530 --> 00:25:23,700
电眼监视器在那边
The surveillance cameras are down here.

290
00:25:23,700 --> 00:25:25,400
我们会尽量努力搜索
We'll dredge the river, but with that current,

291
00:25:25,400 --> 00:25:27,800
不过可能找不到尸体了
I doubt we'll find the body.

292
00:25:31,580 --> 00:25:33,180
为什么?
Why?

293
00:25:33,180 --> 00:25:36,400
天啊! 为什么
Oh, why?

294
00:25:37,350 --> 00:25:39,690
我不敢相信!
I just can't believe it.

295
00:25:39,690 --> 00:25:42,360
同事这么多年了
Two years working in the same office.

296
00:25:43,060 --> 00:25:47,050
他和我情同父子  有如手足
He was like my father... my brother...

297
00:25:47,190 --> 00:25:49,960
我俩简直就是哥儿们
...or a cousin that visits a lot.

298
00:25:49,960 --> 00:25:52,320
艾德华  你要节哀
Get a grip, Edward.

299
00:25:53,400 --> 00:25:55,470
我在他房间发现这个
I found this in my cubicle.

300
00:25:55,470 --> 00:25:57,500
就是他亲笔写的
You'll find the handwriting matches his,

301
00:25:57,500 --> 00:26:00,350
连遣词用字都一样
as does the sentence structure.

302
00:26:03,540 --> 00:26:06,410
我无法再待在这里了
I couldn't possibly continue on here.

303
00:26:06,410 --> 00:26:10,680
这么多痛苦的回忆
The memories....

304
00:26:11,450 --> 00:26:14,590
这是昨晚的监视器记录
This is last night's security log.

305
00:26:14,590 --> 00:26:16,980
那是史帝雷
There's Stickley.

306
00:26:21,900 --> 00:26:23,770
事实很清楚了
Pretty cut and dry.

307
00:26:24,130 --> 00:26:26,560
别矣! 这个残酷的世界!

308
00:26:29,400 --> 00:26:32,250
确实是自杀无疑
Yes, definitely suicide.

309
00:26:32,770 --> 00:26:36,070
谢谢您合作  我们会保持联络
Thanks very much for your help, Bruce. We'll be in touch.

310
00:26:39,480 --> 00:26:42,750
史帝雷自杀毫无道理
Stickley's suicide doesn't make sense.

311
00:26:42,750 --> 00:26:44,850
全额保险给付给他家庭
I want full benefits for his family.

312
00:26:44,850 --> 00:26:47,260
可是自杀死亡保险不理赔
Suicide's not covered by our policy.

313
00:26:47,260 --> 00:26:48,920
我知道  全额给付
I know. Full benefits.

314
00:26:48,920 --> 00:26:51,160
记者一直打电话来询问
Gossip Gerty called 32 times.

315
00:26:51,160 --> 00:26:53,090
你准备带谁参加慈善马戏表演
Who are you taking to the Charity Circus?

316
00:26:53,090 --> 00:26:55,970
我决定了会告诉你  这是什么
I'll let you know. What's this?

317
00:26:55,970 --> 00:26:57,420
不知道
I don't know.

318
00:26:57,600 --> 00:26:59,370
不知是谁送来的
I didn't see anyone.

319
00:27:08,610 --> 00:27:11,150
看着我脸上的数字
"If you look at the numbers on my face...

320
00:27:11,150 --> 00:27:13,960
你永远找不到13
"...you won't find 13 anyplace."

321
00:27:14,420 --> 00:27:15,910
真恶心
That's hideous.

322
00:27:15,920 --> 00:27:17,510
这什么意思
What does it mean?

323
00:27:17,520 --> 00:27:19,320
这个是谜语
It's a riddle.

324
00:27:19,320 --> 00:27:22,160
脸上的数字...13
"Numbers on my face...13."

325
00:27:22,160 --> 00:27:23,560
一到十二
1 through 12.

326
00:27:23,560 --> 00:27:25,610
答案是时钟
The answer is a clock.

327
00:27:25,630 --> 00:27:28,330
谁会没事送个谜语给你?
Who would send you a riddle?

328
00:27:28,330 --> 00:27:31,440
这个嘛...倒也是个谜
That, Maggie... is the riddle.

329
00:28:15,580 --> 00:28:17,980
猜猜我今天干了什么好事
Guess what I did today?

330
00:28:44,710 --> 00:28:47,070
韦恩大老板
Wayne Manor.

331
00:28:56,120 --> 00:28:57,710
走着瞧
See you soon.

332
00:29:28,760 --> 00:29:31,570
我约了梅博士  谢谢
Dr. Meridian, please. Thank you.

333
00:30:02,360 --> 00:30:05,460
我...大概来早了
I... guess I'm early.

334
00:30:06,130 --> 00:30:08,310
我和你约了时间
I have an appointment.

335
00:30:08,330 --> 00:30:10,300
我是布鲁斯韦恩
I'm Bruce Wayne.

336
00:30:10,300 --> 00:30:14,470
太好了  那你可以赔我一扇门
Good. You can afford a door.

337
00:30:14,470 --> 00:30:15,790
抱歉
I'm sorry.

338
00:30:17,740 --> 00:30:23,950
我在外面听到声音...
You...sounded like you were in...

339
00:30:23,950 --> 00:30:29,160
以为你有什么麻烦
...you know, trouble.

340
00:30:30,060 --> 00:30:32,290
这是我宣泄暴力的方式
I prefer healthy expressions of violence

341
00:30:32,290 --> 00:30:35,170
以免我把门给拆了
as opposed to breaking in.

342
00:30:35,470 --> 00:30:36,570
好吧
So...

343
00:30:36,930 --> 00:30:39,880
有什么可效劳的吗?
...how can I help you?

344
00:30:42,400 --> 00:30:45,270
有人不断寄情书给我
Someone's been sending me love letters.

345
00:30:45,270 --> 00:30:49,480
一封寄到办公室  一封寄到家
One at my office and one at my home.

346
00:30:49,480 --> 00:30:53,710
戈登局长说可以听听您的高见
Commissioner Gordon thought you might give me your opinion.

347
00:30:58,180 --> 00:30:58,640
时钟
A clock.

348
00:30:59,490 --> 00:31:00,250
时钟
Clock.

349
00:31:04,360 --> 00:31:08,060
把我折断  摩擦我的头
"Tear one off and scratch my head...

350
00:31:08,060 --> 00:31:11,320
红头随后成黑头
"...what once was red is black instead."

351
00:31:13,130 --> 00:31:14,270
火柴
A match.

352
00:31:19,410 --> 00:31:22,470
我看这家伙是个狂人
My opinion: this letter writer is a wacko.

353
00:31:22,610 --> 00:31:23,820
狂人?
Wacko?

354
00:31:24,380 --> 00:31:26,150
心理学名词吗?
That a technical term?

355
00:31:26,550 --> 00:31:32,020
典型患者具有沉迷杀人之倾向
Patient may suffer from obsession... with potential homicidal tendencies.

356
00:31:32,020 --> 00:31:33,930
够专业吗?
Is that better for you?

357
00:31:34,090 --> 00:31:35,530
所以基本上你认为...
So, what you're saying is...

358
00:31:35,530 --> 00:31:37,460
这家伙是个疯子
...this guy's a total wacko.

359
00:31:37,460 --> 00:31:39,330
完全正确
Exactly.

360
00:31:40,530 --> 00:31:42,430
他疯狂地对你着迷
He's obsessed with you.

361
00:31:42,430 --> 00:31:45,770
只有摧毁偏执对象能自我救赎
His only escape may be to purge the fixation.

362
00:31:47,040 --> 00:31:48,500
就是把我宰了
To kill me.

363
00:31:48,970 --> 00:31:51,300
看不出来你还蛮有概念的
I think you understand obsession better than you let on.

364
00:31:55,610 --> 00:31:57,380
喜欢蝙蝠吗?
You like bats?

365
00:31:58,120 --> 00:31:59,810
那是一种心理测验
That's a Rorschach, Mr. Wayne.

366
00:31:59,820 --> 00:32:01,490
又称墨迹测验
An inkblot.

367
00:32:01,490 --> 00:32:04,250
人们只被想看的墨点所吸引
People see what they want.

368
00:32:04,250 --> 00:32:07,310
问题在于  你喜欢蝙蝠吗?
The question is, do you like bats?

369
00:32:09,590 --> 00:32:11,850
你还在玩这个?
Still playing with dolls?

370
00:32:13,000 --> 00:32:15,600
她是马来人的守护神
She's a Malaysian dream warden.

371
00:32:15,600 --> 00:32:19,240
他们相信她能让你不做恶梦
Some cultures believe she protects you from bad dreams.

372
00:32:19,740 --> 00:32:22,620
你一定觉得有点可笑
It's silly to you, I'm sure.

373
00:32:26,310 --> 00:32:28,780
你看起来不太好
You look so sad.

374
00:32:29,510 --> 00:32:31,910
需要一个娃娃吗?
Do you need one?

375
00:32:32,020 --> 00:32:34,720
我? 谢了  有此必要吗?
Me? No. Why would I?

376
00:32:36,150 --> 00:32:40,130
你看起来十分心神不宁
You're not exactly what you seem, are you?

377
00:32:40,130 --> 00:32:43,840
你到底为什么来此找我?
What is it you really came here for?

378
00:32:44,760 --> 00:32:47,200
呃  时间到了
Yikes, time's up.

379
00:32:48,570 --> 00:32:51,100
通常这句话该由我来说
That's usually my line.

380
00:32:51,100 --> 00:32:52,740
我真希望能再多聊会儿
I'd love to stay here chatting.

381
00:32:52,740 --> 00:32:55,270
真的吗?
Would you?

382
00:32:55,270 --> 00:32:56,110
我可不太相信
I'm not so sure.

383
00:32:56,110 --> 00:33:00,750
我希望你把这身衣服脱掉
I must get you out of those clothes.

384
00:33:00,750 --> 00:33:02,050
什么?
Excuse me?

385
00:33:02,050 --> 00:33:04,350
换上黑色晚礼服
And into a black dress.

